\pard\pardeftab720\qc\partightenfactor0
\cf3 Illustration of you seeing someone across the street in a busy intersection and it's only for a few seconds. You wave, they don't see you or at least acknowledge you and you move on.\'a0 When you mention you saw the person to your spouse they inform you that person is actually in another country and they don't know who you saw but it wasn't them. How hard do you argue that? Unless you just like to argue or are super prideful...not much. I mean you didn't get a clear look and let's be honest sometimes we all think we see something we really didn't see...and so you move on..Now, change the story a little bit. You see the same person, wave at them, they do acknowledge you and you end up talking to them for 30 minutes...then someone tries to tell you that this person is in another country. Unless you believe in Ghosts or the paranormal, which I don't btw, you're going to argue with them. Same story for the most part the only difference is the clarity with which you saw and engaged with the person.\cf2 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf2 \
